summary: An ordinance amending section 1 of Ordinance No. 21655 of the City of Seattle, entitled: "An ordinance providing for the placing of wires carrying electrical energy or used for telephone or telegraph or other electrical energy in the City of Seattle, underground in certain districts within a specified time, and providing penalties for violations of the provisions of this ordinance", approved August 12, 1909, as amended by Ordinance No. 33935, approved November 11, 1914.
